"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"[![Andre Cronje](https://miro.medium.com/fit/c/56/56/2\\\\*Vjiwqoib1HcKLdkM1xwp_g.jpeg)](https://andrecronje.medium.com/?source=post_page-----54d82961a2a0--------------------------------)\\n\\nSynthetix [SIP-120](https://sips.synthetix.io/sips/sip-120/) required the development of easily integratable on-chain oracles;\\n\\nWith the advent of Uniswap V3, we have 0 maintenance on-chain TWAP price feeds. The TWAP code however can be tricky to use, to help simplify this, [Brett Sun](https://github.com/sohkai) developed on-chain, easy to use oracles;\\n\\nContract: [0x0F1f5A87f99f0918e6C81F16E59F3518698221Ff](https://etherscan.io/address/0x0F1f5A87f99f0918e6C81F16E59F3518698221Ff#readContract)\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/1\\\\*3AE5KXZLX67J5omvcb0OWw.png)\\n\\nSolidity Implementation: [here](https://gist.github.com/andrecronje/962932e2301f0b217c13f1ed0b7ca594)\\n\\nThe easiest way to use is to simply call `assetToAsset` however, this will route through `WETH`, alternatively, use `assetToAssetThruRoute`, which specifies a non default route.\\n\\nFurther to the above, a [multiprice-oracle](https://github.com/sohkai/multiprice-oracle/tree/main/packages/evm) was also developed;\\n\\nContract: [0x1f53a354b726Dcd1FC8053182a46dE6b9995740F](https://etherscan.io/address/0x1f53a354b726dcd1fc8053182a46de6b9995740f#readContract)\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/1\\\\*mpK-Kgie-FWFOaKOxgbJrQ.png)\\n\\nUsage of the multiprice oracle will provide feeds from uniswap v3 twap, v3 spot, v2 spot, sushi spot, and chainlink, and currently being deployed to support Band Protocol.\\n\\nHopefully this makes querying on-chain price feeds easier for teams.\\n\",\"timestamp\":1634229641,\"title\":\"Easy on-chain Oracles - Andre Cronje - Medium\"},\"digest\":\"hJkeWwNK_bbRYEWQ_HPLgZkKf5OwnA8s1GMQFQLnqHk\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x9747D92f03A5093A15260B9cB1a26F32E248db18\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_op